{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M6vWTYgGxiKCjUTYWRg2gE","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: PRD-556.1\n3\ttitle: Scaffold cli/ package with __init__, _parser, _shared, and main\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: medium\n7\teffort: s\n8\tcapability: simple\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-556-modularize-cli]]\"\n10\tdepends_on: []\n11\tblocks:\n12\t  - \"[[PRD-556.2-move-new]]\"\n13\t  - \"[[PRD-556.3-move-status]]\"\n14\t  - \"[[PRD-556.4-move-cleanup]]\"\n15\t  - \"[[PRD-556.5-move-next]]\"\n16\t  - \"[[PRD-556.6-move-validate]]\"\n17\t  - \"[[PRD-556.7-move-tree]]\"\n18\t  - \"[[PRD-556.8-move-children]]\"\n19\t  - \"[[PRD-556.9-move-orphans]]\"\n20\t  - \"[[PRD-556.10-move-undecomposed]]\"\n21\t  - \"[[PRD-556.11-move-conflicts]]\"\n22\t  - \"[[PRD-556.12-move-list-workflows]]\"\n23\t  - \"[[PRD-556.13-move-assign]]\"\n24\t  - \"[[PRD-556.14-move-normalize]]\"\n25\t  - \"[[PRD-556.15-move-plan]]\"\n26\t  - \"[[PRD-556.16-move-run]]\"\n27\t  - \"[[PRD-556.17-move-reconcile]]\"\n28\timpacts:\n29\t  - src/darkfactory/cli/__init__.py\n30\t  - src/darkfactory/cli/_parser.py\n31\t  - src/darkfactory/cli/_shared.py\n32\t  - src/darkfactory/cli/_shared_test.py\n33\t  - src/darkfactory/cli/main.py\n34\t  - src/darkfactory/cli/main_test.py\n35\t  - src/darkfactory/cli.py\n36\tworkflow:\n37\ttarget_version:\n38\tcreated: 2026-04-08\n39\tupdated: 2026-04-09\n40\ttags:\n41\t  - refactor\n42\t  - organization\n43\t  - cli\n44\t---\n45\t\n46\t# Scaffold cli/ package with __init__, _parser, _shared, and main\n47\t\n48\t## Summary\n49\t\n50\tConvert `src/darkfactory/cli.py` from a single module into a Python package by creating the `src/darkfactory/cli/` directory with `__init__.py`, `_parser.py`, `_shared.py`, and `main.py`. Move the shared helpers, `build_parser()`, `_configure_logging()`, `main()`, and the module-level constants into their respective new modules. `__init__.py` re-exports `main` and `build_parser` so all existing import sites continue to work unchanged.\n51\t\n52\t**No subcommand functions are moved in this task.** All `cmd_*` functions remain importable from the old location via `__init__.py` re-exports. This is an empty functional change — all tests pass before and after.\n53\t\n54\t## Requirements\n55\t\n56\t1. Create `src/darkfactory/cli/` as a Python package.\n57\t2. Move `_find_repo_root`, `_load`, `_default_prd_dir`, `_default_workflows_dir`, `_load_workflows_or_fail`, `_action_sort_key` into `src/darkfactory/cli/_shared.py`. Also move `PRIORITY_ORDER`, `EFFORT_ORDER`, `CAPABILITY_ORDER`.\n58\t3. Create `src/darkfactory/cli/_shared_test.py` with unit tests for the shared helpers (at minimum `_find_repo_root`, `_load`, `_action_sort_key`).\n59\t4. Move `build_parser()` into `src/darkfactory/cli/_parser.py`. It imports `cmd_*` functions from `__init__.py` (or directly from submodules once they exist).\n60\t5. Move `main(argv)` and `_configure_logging(verbose)` into `src/darkfactory/cli/main.py`.\n61\t6. Create `src/darkfactory/cli/main_test.py` with a basic smoke test for the entry point.\n62\t7. `src/darkfactory/cli/__init__.py` imports from `_shared`, `_parser`, and `main`, and re-exports the public API (`main`, `build_parser`). It also holds all `cmd_*` functions temporarily (moved verbatim from old file) until later PRDs extract them.\n63\t8. Every existing `from darkfactory.cli import X` import site continues to work unchanged.\n64\t9. All existing tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n65\t\n66\t## Technical Approach\n67\t\n68\t### `src/darkfactory/cli/_shared.py`\n69\t\n70\tMove from the old `cli.py`:\n71\t- `PRIORITY_ORDER`, `EFFORT_ORDER`, `CAPABILITY_ORDER` — module-level dicts\n72\t- `_find_repo_root(start: Path) -> Path`\n73\t- `_default_prd_dir() -> Path`\n74\t- `_default_workflows_dir() -> Path`\n75\t- `_load_workflows_or_fail(workflows_dir: Path) -> dict[str, Workflow]`\n76\t- `_action_sort_key(prd: PRD) -> tuple[int, int, tuple[int, ...]]`\n77\t- `_load(prd_dir: Path) -> dict[str, PRD]`\n78\t\n79\t### `src/darkfactory/cli/_parser.py`\n80\t\n81\tMove `build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser` verbatim. It references `cmd_*` functions as `set_defaults(func=cmd_X)` — these will be imported from the package's `__init__.py` initially.\n82\t\n83\t### `src/darkfactory/cli/main.py`\n84\t\n85\tMove:\n86\t- `_configure_logging(verbose: bool) -> None`\n87\t- `main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int`\n88\t\n89\t### `src/darkfactory/cli/__init__.py`\n90\t\n91\t```python\n92\t\"\"\"CLI package — re-export hub.\n93\t\n94\tHolds cmd_* functions temporarily until extracted by subsequent PRDs.\n95\tRe-exports main and build_parser for backwards compatibility.\n96\t\"\"\"\n97\tfrom darkfactory.cli._shared import (\n98\t    PRIORITY_ORDER, EFFORT_ORDER, CAPABILITY_ORDER,\n99\t    _find_repo_root, _default_prd_dir, _default_workflows_dir,\n100\t    _load_workflows_or_fail, _action_sort_key, _load,\n101\t)\n102\tfrom darkfactory.cli._parser import build_parser\n103\tfrom darkfactory.cli.main import main\n104\t\n105\t# All cmd_* functions live here temporarily...\n106\t\n107\t__all__ = [\"main\", \"build_parser\"]\n108\t```\n109\t\n110\t### Migration strategy\n111\t\n112\t1. Delete `src/darkfactory/cli.py`.\n113\t2. Create `src/darkfactory/cli/` directory.\n114\t3. Create `_shared.py`, `_parser.py`, `main.py`, `__init__.py`.\n115\t4. `__init__.py` initially holds all `cmd_*` implementations (moved verbatim) plus imports from internal modules.\n116\t5. Verify all tests pass — this is a no-op refactor at this point.\n117\t\n118\t## Acceptance Criteria\n119\t\n120\t- [ ] AC-1: `src/darkfactory/cli/` exists as a Python package with `__init__.py`, `_shared.py`, `_parser.py`, and `main.py`.\n121\t- [ ] AC-2: `_shared.py` contains all shared helpers and constants listed above.\n122\t- [ ] AC-3: `_parser.py` contains `build_parser()`.\n123\t- [ ] AC-4: `main.py` contains `main()` and `_configure_logging()`.\n124\t- [ ] AC-5: `_shared_test.py` has unit tests for the shared helpers.\n125\t- [ ] AC-6: `main_test.py` has a smoke test for the entry point.\n126\t- [ ] AC-7: Every existing `from darkfactory.cli import X` import site still resolves.\n127\t- [ ] AC-8: All existing tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n128\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6a3db6e8-ce1a-4c6b-ad07-39bb96d60951","uuid":"53a81fb4-2080-4434-9e52-c7d7c60d5fd2","timestamp":"2026-04-09T07:54:55.804Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.darkfactory/prds/PRD-556.1-scaffold-cli-package.md","content":"---\nid: PRD-556.1\ntitle: Scaffold cli/ package with __init__, _parser, _shared, and main\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: s\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-556-modularize-cli]]\"\ndepends_on: []\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-556.2-move-new]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.3-move-status]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.4-move-cleanup]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.5-move-next]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.6-move-validate]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.7-move-tree]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.8-move-children]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.9-move-orphans]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.10-move-undecomposed]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.11-move-conflicts]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.12-move-list-workflows]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.13-move-assign]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.14-move-normalize]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.15-move-plan]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.16-move-run]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-556.17-move-reconcile]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/cli/__init__.py\n  - src/darkfactory/cli/_parser.py\n  - src/darkfactory/cli/_shared.py\n  - src/darkfactory/cli/_shared_test.py\n  - src/darkfactory/cli/main.py\n  - src/darkfactory/cli/main_test.py\n  - src/darkfactory/cli.py\nworkflow:\ntarget_version:\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-09\ntags:\n  - refactor\n  - organization\n  - cli\n---\n\n# Scaffold cli/ package with __init__, _parser, _shared, and main\n\n## Summary\n\nConvert `src/darkfactory/cli.py` from a single module into a Python package by creating the `src/darkfactory/cli/` directory with `__init__.py`, `_parser.py`, `_shared.py`, and `main.py`. Move the shared helpers, `build_parser()`, `_configure_logging()`, `main()`, and the module-level constants into their respective new modules. `__init__.py` re-exports `main` and `build_parser` so all existing import sites continue to work unchanged.\n\n**No subcommand functions are moved in this task.** All `cmd_*` functions remain importable from the old location via `__init__.py` re-exports. This is an empty functional change — all tests pass before and after.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Create `src/darkfactory/cli/` as a Python package.\n2. Move `_find_repo_root`, `_load`, `_default_prd_dir`, `_default_workflows_dir`, `_load_workflows_or_fail`, `_action_sort_key` into `src/darkfactory/cli/_shared.py`. Also move `PRIORITY_ORDER`, `EFFORT_ORDER`, `CAPABILITY_ORDER`.\n3. Create `src/darkfactory/cli/_shared_test.py` with unit tests for the shared helpers (at minimum `_find_repo_root`, `_load`, `_action_sort_key`).\n4. Move `build_parser()` into `src/darkfactory/cli/_parser.py`. It imports `cmd_*` functions from `__init__.py` (or directly from submodules once they exist).\n5. Move `main(argv)` and `_configure_logging(verbose)` into `src/darkfactory/cli/main.py`.\n6. Create `src/darkfactory/cli/main_test.py` with a basic smoke test for the entry point.\n7. `src/darkfactory/cli/__init__.py` imports from `_shared`, `_parser`, and `main`, and re-exports the public API (`main`, `build_parser`). It also holds all `cmd_*` functions temporarily (moved verbatim from old file) until later PRDs extract them.\n8. Every existing `from darkfactory.cli import X` import site continues to work unchanged.\n9. All existing tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/cli/_shared.py`\n\nMove from the old `cli.py`:\n- `PRIORITY_ORDER`, `EFFORT_ORDER`, `CAPABILITY_ORDER` — module-level dicts\n- `_find_repo_root(start: Path) -> Path`\n- `_default_prd_dir() -> Path`\n- `_default_workflows_dir() -> Path`\n- `_load_workflows_or_fail(workflows_dir: Path) -> dict[str, Workflow]`\n- `_action_sort_key(prd: PRD) -> tuple[int, int, tuple[int, ...]]`\n- `_load(prd_dir: Path) -> dict[str, PRD]`\n\n### `src/darkfactory/cli/_parser.py`\n\nMove `build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser` verbatim. It references `cmd_*` functions as `set_defaults(func=cmd_X)` — these will be imported from the package's `__init__.py` initially.\n\n### `src/darkfactory/cli/main.py`\n\nMove:\n- `_configure_logging(verbose: bool) -> None`\n- `main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int`\n\n### `src/darkfactory/cli/__init__.py`\n\n```python\n\"\"\"CLI package — re-export hub.\n\nHolds cmd_* functions temporarily until extracted by subsequent PRDs.\nRe-exports main and build_parser for backwards compatibility.\n\"\"\"\nfrom darkfactory.cli._shared import (\n    PRIORITY_ORDER, EFFORT_ORDER, CAPABILITY_ORDER,\n    _find_repo_root, _default_prd_dir, _default_workflows_dir,\n    _load_workflows_or_fail, _action_sort_key, _load,\n)\nfrom darkfactory.cli._parser import build_parser\nfrom darkfactory.cli.main import main\n\n# All cmd_* functions live here temporarily...\n\n__all__ = [\"main\", \"build_parser\"]\n```\n\n### Migration strategy\n\n1. Delete `src/darkfactory/cli.py`.\n2. Create `src/darkfactory/cli/` directory.\n3. Create `_shared.py`, `_parser.py`, `main.py`, `__init__.py`.\n4. `__init__.py` initially holds all `cmd_*` implementations (moved verbatim) plus imports from internal modules.\n5. Verify all tests pass — this is a no-op refactor at this point.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `src/darkfactory/cli/` exists as a Python package with `__init__.py`, `_shared.py`, `_parser.py`, and `main.py`.\n- [ ] AC-2: `_shared.py` contains all shared helpers and constants listed above.\n- [ ] AC-3: `_parser.py` contains `build_parser()`.\n- [ ] AC-4: `main.py` contains `main()` and `_configure_logging()`.\n- [ ] AC-5: `_shared_test.py` has unit tests for the shared helpers.\n- [ ] AC-6: `main_test.py` has a smoke test for the entry point.\n- [ ] AC-7: Every existing `from darkfactory.cli import X` import site still resolves.\n- [ ] AC-8: All existing tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n","numLines":128,"startLine":1,"totalLines":128}}}
